			<name>
				<baseName xml:lang="en">Waste fiber fabric</baseName>
				<baseName xml:lang="zh">废弃纤维织物</baseName>
			</name>
			<common:synonyms xml:lang="en">Unknown fiber blends; Mixed material fabric; Fast fashion fabric</common:synonyms>
			<common:synonyms xml:lang="zh">Unknown fiber blends; Mixed material fabric; Fast fashion fabric</common:synonyms>
			<classificationInformation>
				<common:classification name="ILCD 1.1" classes="../ILCDClassification.xml">
					<common:class level="0">Wastes</common:class>
					<common:class level="1">Construction waste</common:class>
				</common:classification>
			</classificationInformation>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="en">Waste fiber fabric refers to textiles made from unknown fiber blends, often used in the fast fashion industry. These fabrics, including polyester, spandex, viscose, and nylon, are problematic in the recycling process due to their mixed materials. They make up 8% of municipal waste and take decades to biodegrade, releasing microplastics. Initiatives are focusing on reducing textile waste both post-consumer and pre-consumer, which originates in the design and development process.</common:generalComment>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="zh">废纤维织物是指由未知纤维混纺制成的纺织品，常用于快时尚行业。这些织物，包括涤纶、氨纶、粘胶纤维和尼龙，由于材料混合，在回收过程中存在问题。它们占城市垃圾的 8%，需要几十年才能生物降解，释放出微塑料。这些举措的重点是减少消费后和消费前的纺织品废料，这源于设计和开发过程。</common:generalComment>
		</dataSetInformation>
